<subSubSection id="04642BECAFB2246227B4CD81005D1FA9" pageId="0" pageNumber="187" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B26E9556E814E93BB42235A07BA73A6" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1099340FEC3938E77F4083BD171F621E" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">
<emphasis id="3FD64BC40B5C5DBB589FEACB66C79183" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Male. Coloration</emphasis>
: Body yellowish brown or brown (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="F04C7A664F2D840034EE067B68CC6161" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Centrocolumna ericea gen. et sp. nov., male: A holotype, dorsal view; B holotype, ventral view; C head, ventral view; D pronotum; E maxillary palp; F front femur, ventral view; G seventh abdominal tergite; H tegmen; I wing; J supra-anal plate, ventral view; K left phallomere; L median phallomere; M right phallomere; N subgenital plate, dorsal view. Scale bars: 10 mm (A, B), 1 mm (C, D), 2 mm (H, I), 0.5 mm (E-G, J-N)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e62469.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/690402" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">2A, B</figureCitation>
). Ocelli pale yellow. Antennae yellowish brown with base pale yellow. Maxillary palps with fourth and fifth palpomeres yellow brown, others pale yellow (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="450484E6F275C7FFC859D6325C78E05A" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Centrocolumna ericea gen. et sp. nov., male: A holotype, dorsal view; B holotype, ventral view; C head, ventral view; D pronotum; E maxillary palp; F front femur, ventral view; G seventh abdominal tergite; H tegmen; I wing; J supra-anal plate, ventral view; K left phallomere; L median phallomere; M right phallomere; N subgenital plate, dorsal view. Scale bars: 10 mm (A, B), 1 mm (C, D), 2 mm (H, I), 0.5 mm (E-G, J-N)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e62469.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/690402" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">2E</figureCitation>
). Pronotum yellowish brown, with a light-colored vertical stripe at disk (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="EF4C73CF43DB847F22C7C44CEE694570" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Centrocolumna ericea gen. et sp. nov., male: A holotype, dorsal view; B holotype, ventral view; C head, ventral view; D pronotum; E maxillary palp; F front femur, ventral view; G seventh abdominal tergite; H tegmen; I wing; J supra-anal plate, ventral view; K left phallomere; L median phallomere; M right phallomere; N subgenital plate, dorsal view. Scale bars: 10 mm (A, B), 1 mm (C, D), 2 mm (H, I), 0.5 mm (E-G, J-N)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e62469.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/690402" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">2C, D</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis id="627767EDED38F8BDCB62BEE55582CF42" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Head</emphasis>
: Interocular space slightly less than ocelli width and distinctly narrower than width of antennal sockets. Third and fifth maxillary palpomeres about same length, and slightly longer than the fourth (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="03B9C3856A4DD607E32E6D83AFCFDE20" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Centrocolumna ericea gen. et sp. nov., male: A holotype, dorsal view; B holotype, ventral view; C head, ventral view; D pronotum; E maxillary palp; F front femur, ventral view; G seventh abdominal tergite; H tegmen; I wing; J supra-anal plate, ventral view; K left phallomere; L median phallomere; M right phallomere; N subgenital plate, dorsal view. Scale bars: 10 mm (A, B), 1 mm (C, D), 2 mm (H, I), 0.5 mm (E-G, J-N)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e62469.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/690402" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">2E</figureCitation>
). Posterior margin of pronotum slightly convex in the middle (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="0648CCBB3ACCB5EF8879015EDDC11815" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Centrocolumna ericea gen. et sp. nov., male: A holotype, dorsal view; B holotype, ventral view; C head, ventral view; D pronotum; E maxillary palp; F front femur, ventral view; G seventh abdominal tergite; H tegmen; I wing; J supra-anal plate, ventral view; K left phallomere; L median phallomere; M right phallomere; N subgenital plate, dorsal view. Scale bars: 10 mm (A, B), 1 mm (C, D), 2 mm (H, I), 0.5 mm (E-G, J-N)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e62469.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/690402" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">2D</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis id="B14C12284A97D8685653466CBD71684B" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Tegmina and hindwings</emphasis>
: Both fully developed, extending beyond end of abdomen (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="424F46CCA29F6F39645B8B7272D4B56D" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Centrocolumna ericea gen. et sp. nov., male: A holotype, dorsal view; B holotype, ventral view; C head, ventral view; D pronotum; E maxillary palp; F front femur, ventral view; G seventh abdominal tergite; H tegmen; I wing; J supra-anal plate, ventral view; K left phallomere; L median phallomere; M right phallomere; N subgenital plate, dorsal view. Scale bars: 10 mm (A, B), 1 mm (C, D), 2 mm (H, I), 0.5 mm (E-G, J-N)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e62469.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/690402" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">2H, I</figureCitation>
). RP of hindwings with branches near the middle, CuA curved as 
<normalizedToken id="E5DB1A5969D4A3A4EBA3D31269AD284D" originalValue="“S”">&quot;S&quot;</normalizedToken>
with 4 complete and 3 incomplete branches (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="7C28FECBB3D82AA19C74AFBF5D0B3CE1" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Centrocolumna ericea gen. et sp. nov., male: A holotype, dorsal view; B holotype, ventral view; C head, ventral view; D pronotum; E maxillary palp; F front femur, ventral view; G seventh abdominal tergite; H tegmen; I wing; J supra-anal plate, ventral view; K left phallomere; L median phallomere; M right phallomere; N subgenital plate, dorsal view. Scale bars: 10 mm (A, B), 1 mm (C, D), 2 mm (H, I), 0.5 mm (E-G, J-N)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e62469.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/690402" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">2I</figureCitation>
); apical triangle small. 
<emphasis id="37A0B2AD7519B11A9554254B742F9B0B" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Legs</emphasis>
: Anteroventral margin of front femur Type A3 (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="F841B30D1BEA2A8761EDFE640E52AAE3" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Centrocolumna ericea gen. et sp. nov., male: A holotype, dorsal view; B holotype, ventral view; C head, ventral view; D pronotum; E maxillary palp; F front femur, ventral view; G seventh abdominal tergite; H tegmen; I wing; J supra-anal plate, ventral view; K left phallomere; L median phallomere; M right phallomere; N subgenital plate, dorsal view. Scale bars: 10 mm (A, B), 1 mm (C, D), 2 mm (H, I), 0.5 mm (E-G, J-N)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e62469.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/690402" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">2F</figureCitation>
), pretarsal claws symmetrical and unspecialized. 
<emphasis id="9D1A42EF6F8F0D4AEF1A2E27759791A0" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Abdominal tergites</emphasis>
: T1 specialized with a setal tuft in the middle; T7 specialized with a pair of shallow fossae and a setal tuft in the middle, two dark brown spots on each side of the tuft (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="C259E32A94D3EA0E9A24FB6B4C8B7D3A" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Centrocolumna ericea gen. et sp. nov., male: A holotype, dorsal view; B holotype, ventral view; C head, ventral view; D pronotum; E maxillary palp; F front femur, ventral view; G seventh abdominal tergite; H tegmen; I wing; J supra-anal plate, ventral view; K left phallomere; L median phallomere; M right phallomere; N subgenital plate, dorsal view. Scale bars: 10 mm (A, B), 1 mm (C, D), 2 mm (H, I), 0.5 mm (E-G, J-N)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e62469.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/690402" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">2G</figureCitation>
). T10 with a median ridge, where a bunch of bristles is born, hind margin broadly and weakly concave. 
<emphasis id="4E11F59CB8670932A3FF45DA7924D6FA" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Paraprocts</emphasis>
: Dissimilar, right one with a long spine and a cockscomb-like process, and left one with a shorter spine-like process distad (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="EF8E43192CD84B370648A55A3220ED77" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Centrocolumna ericea gen. et sp. nov., male: A holotype, dorsal view; B holotype, ventral view; C head, ventral view; D pronotum; E maxillary palp; F front femur, ventral view; G seventh abdominal tergite; H tegmen; I wing; J supra-anal plate, ventral view; K left phallomere; L median phallomere; M right phallomere; N subgenital plate, dorsal view. Scale bars: 10 mm (A, B), 1 mm (C, D), 2 mm (H, I), 0.5 mm (E-G, J-N)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e62469.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/690402" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">2J</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis id="0E049B3F6868E38DF87B9C16D5A06394" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Subgenital plate</emphasis>
: Asymmetrical, styli cone-shaped, the right one located on the apex of a protrusion arising from middle of hind margin, and left one slightly larger and near base of right one (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="C082B9B0CE5233A424DC0BAE63270477" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Centrocolumna ericea gen. et sp. nov., male: A holotype, dorsal view; B holotype, ventral view; C head, ventral view; D pronotum; E maxillary palp; F front femur, ventral view; G seventh abdominal tergite; H tegmen; I wing; J supra-anal plate, ventral view; K left phallomere; L median phallomere; M right phallomere; N subgenital plate, dorsal view. Scale bars: 10 mm (A, B), 1 mm (C, D), 2 mm (H, I), 0.5 mm (E-G, J-N)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e62469.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/690402" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">2N</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis id="EE70D85B564A422C2604DE72CE72F68B" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Male genitalia</emphasis>
: L3 on the left side with a subapical incision (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="A50DDAC1F43408CC67215DA9E3D4A9ED" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Centrocolumna ericea gen. et sp. nov., male: A holotype, dorsal view; B holotype, ventral view; C head, ventral view; D pronotum; E maxillary palp; F front femur, ventral view; G seventh abdominal tergite; H tegmen; I wing; J supra-anal plate, ventral view; K left phallomere; L median phallomere; M right phallomere; N subgenital plate, dorsal view. Scale bars: 10 mm (A, B), 1 mm (C, D), 2 mm (H, I), 0.5 mm (E-G, J-N)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e62469.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/690402" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">2K</figureCitation>
); proximal end of L2vm with an inconspicuous bifurcation, and the apex sharp (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="03A9CA77197218DEEA41FE3E21EA48FA" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Centrocolumna ericea gen. et sp. nov., male: A holotype, dorsal view; B holotype, ventral view; C head, ventral view; D pronotum; E maxillary palp; F front femur, ventral view; G seventh abdominal tergite; H tegmen; I wing; J supra-anal plate, ventral view; K left phallomere; L median phallomere; M right phallomere; N subgenital plate, dorsal view. Scale bars: 10 mm (A, B), 1 mm (C, D), 2 mm (H, I), 0.5 mm (E-G, J-N)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e62469.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/690402" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">2L</figureCitation>
); R2, R3 complex with a Y-shaped sclerite (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="DD8E7144C83DE5D7C94D8567BFF0E3C6" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Centrocolumna ericea gen. et sp. nov., male: A holotype, dorsal view; B holotype, ventral view; C head, ventral view; D pronotum; E maxillary palp; F front femur, ventral view; G seventh abdominal tergite; H tegmen; I wing; J supra-anal plate, ventral view; K left phallomere; L median phallomere; M right phallomere; N subgenital plate, dorsal view. Scale bars: 10 mm (A, B), 1 mm (C, D), 2 mm (H, I), 0.5 mm (E-G, J-N)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e62469.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/690402" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">2M</figureCitation>
). - 
<emphasis id="55DB39A478E45A7D7F844711130A09B3" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Female.</emphasis>
Like male (except for postabdomen).
</paragraph>
